initial_story:
Firefighters and police were seen outside the office of Mike Freer MP

Police are investigating a suspected arson attack at the office of North London Conservative MP Mike Freer.

A fire broke out at the rear of the North Finchley and Golders Green MP's constituency office at around 19:00 on Christmas Eve.

The Met Police confirmed it is investigating the fire.

Mr Freer told the BBC the fire happened at the rear of the premises and no one was in the building at the time of the incident.

He continued: "The police and fire brigade were on the scene in minutes and have been incredible in their response."

London Fire Brigade (LFB) confirmed the fire started in a shed outside the office before spreading to the rest of the building.

An LFB spokesperson said: "An external shed was destroyed by fire. Part of the first, second and third floors of the property were also damaged by the blaze."

In a statement, a Metropolitan Police spokesperson said: "The cause of the fire is under investigation as it is believed it may have been started deliberately. There have been no arrests."

Pictures posted on social media showed Metropolitan Police and LFB vehicles at the premises on Sunday evening.

Mr Freer has represented the North London constituency since 2010.

He is parliamentary under-secretary of state for courts and legal services, a junior role in the Ministry of Justice.

Pictures show the fire spread to an office inside the building

The firefighters and police arrived at the scene of the suspected arson attack at the office of Mike Freer MP. The flames had already engulfed the building, sending thick smoke into the night sky. As the firefighters began to battle the blaze, the police began to investigate the scene. It was clear that this was no accident. The evidence suggested that someone had deliberately set the fire.

The investigators began to look for clues. They searched the surrounding area for signs of a possible suspect. They found a small piece of evidence that could be the key to the case. It was a piece of fabric that had been charred by the flames. The investigators took the fabric back to the lab for analysis. They discovered that the fabric had been dipped in a flammable liquid. This was the evidence that they needed to catch the culprit.

The investigators began to question people in the area. They found a witness who had seen a man running away from the scene of the crime. The witness was able to provide a description of the suspect. The investigators were able to use this information to track down the suspect. They eventually found him hiding in an abandoned building. He was arrested and taken into custody.

The investigators were able to piece together the evidence and build a strong case against the suspect. He was eventually charged with arson and sentenced to a long prison term. The investigators had solved the case and brought justice to the people of North London.

It was a dark and stormy night. The rain was pouring down in sheets, and the wind was howling like a banshee. The streets were deserted, and the only sound was the occasional crack of lightning.

Suddenly, a figure emerged from the shadows. It was a tall, thin man, dressed all in black. He was carrying a large bag, and he was moving with a purposeful stride.

He made his way to a small house on the outskirts of town. He knocked on the door, and a woman answered.

"Yes?" she said.

"I'm here to see your husband," the man said.

The woman looked at him with a puzzled expression.

"He's not here," she said.

The man frowned.

"Where is he?" he asked.

The woman hesitated for a moment.

"He's gone," she said.

The man's frown deepened.

"Gone where?" he asked.

The woman shrugged.

"I don't know," she said.

The man's eyes narrowed.

"Are you sure?" he asked.

The woman nodded.

"Yes, I'm sure," she said.

The man's face darkened.

"I don't believe you," he said.

The woman took a step back.

"What are you going to do?" she asked.

The man reached into his bag and pulled out a gun.

"I'm going to find him," he said.

The woman's eyes widened in fear.

"Please, don't hurt me," she said.

The man ignored her. He turned and walked away into the night.

"Why?" I asked.

"Because it is time," he said.
